			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DR-19430314-IT_01.jpg"/>
			<p>R. Representation of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3175395/italian-republic.html">Italy</placeName> for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/390903/hellenic-republic.html">Greece</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/264371/athens.html">Athens</placeName></p>
			<p>c.c.</p>
			<p>R. <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005042">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</orgName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3169070/rome.html">Rome</placeName></p>
			<p>Classified</p>
			<p><date when="1943-05-14">14th March 1943</date>,</p>
			<p>Class./<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-330" type="subject">Measures</term> against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/734077/thessaloniki.html">Thessaloniki</placeName>.</p>
			<p>The Jews of Thessaloniki have been entirely <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-332" type="subject">excluded
					from any activity</term> and have for over a week now been confined to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>, unable <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">to leave</term> it for any reason whatsoever.</p>
			<p>Their entire <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-333" type="subject">property has been seized</term> and will
				be managed through <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-590" type="subject">fiduciaries</term>, who will have
				to deposit the proceeds from sales in a special blocked account. So far it is not precisely known if part of the sums thus obtained
				will be used for the sustenance of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-888" type="subject">destitute
					Jews</term>, who are the great majority.</p>
			<p>Several sources confirm that their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">transfer</term> to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> should start anytime now.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1032" type="subject">German authorities</term> have requested from the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish Community</term> a list of 120 prominent
				persons to be regarded as hostages. In this list there are also 12 Italian citizens of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-365" type="subject">Jewish race</term> who, together with the others, were
				summoned on the 7th inst. to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Community`s</term>
				premises where a German officer gave a short speech and explained that they would answer with their own persons for any accident or
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-246" type="subject">act of sabotage</term> that might occur. He
				added that it would have been his duty to intern them at once in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496"
					type="subject">concentration camp</term>, but that due to the assurances given by the Chief <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">Rabbi</term> he would let them stay free for the time
				being. The said prominent persons are also required to provide out of their own means for the needs of the poorer <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>.</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DR-19430314-IT_02.jpg"/>
			<p>I have approached the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1084" type="subject">Befehlshaber</term> and was
				able to obtain his assurance that the Italian citizens will be removed from said list and we reached an understanding that they will
				no longer comply with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">the instructions and the
					orders</term> they should still receive through the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872"
					type="subject">Jewish Community</term>.</p>
			<p>Due to the zeal displayed by the offices in charge of carrying out the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-330" type="subject">adopted measures</term>, I find myself compelled all
				the time to undertake steps to prevent our fellow-citizens from being hampered in their usual commercial activity. Until now, however,
				there have been only inevitable repercussions of a very limited and modest relevance.</p>
			<p>The sudden removal from town life of over 50 thousand people, who for centuries had continuously been engaged in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">important activities</term>, has been the cause of
				serious inconveniences. A great many services that were provided almost <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">exclusively by Jews</term> are now missing, and the
				price of commodities has increased sharply, to the point where the local <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> has been clamouring for severe steps
				against the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/390903/hellenic-republic.html">Greek</placeName> merchants who exploit the present
				moment.</p>
			<p>Due to the closing of the great many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-890" type="subject">Jewish
					shops</term>, to the diminished traffic in the streets and to the scarcity of public in cinemas and in restaurants-cafés, the town
				has acquired a look pervaded by a sense of sadness.</p>
			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-DR-19430314-IT_03.jpg"/>
			<p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/390903/hellenic-republic.html">Greek</placeName> element, except for the merchants who have
				seen their dreaded competitors disappear, displays no enthusiasm for all that is being done, quite the opposite, they worry about the
				immediate and future consequences.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> who had been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">issued by us with a pass</term> have been prevented by
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">German</term> authorities from reaching our
				zone. I have enquired to see if some exception might not be granted for the most serious cases, but have received a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1033" type="subject">negative answer</term>, in fact I was told that they
				would request that those who had already moved into our territory be returned to them.</p>
			<p>(<persName ref="#ehri_dr_zamboni_guelfo">Guelfo Zamboni</persName> )</p>
